General comment:
The whole section is crosscut by calcite veins.  Shows evidence of slight metamorphism from rotate clasts (appear to be silica?) and flow of matrix around clasts.  Bedding contains calcite along planes. Lithology is difficult to describe. Main components are re-cristallized ( first calcite and second  silica cements) sedimentary clast and sedimentary bedding structures probably from former silt and sandstones. Eventually two-stage cementation with low temperature calcite at the beginning and higher temperature silica as second stage.
